## Listing

> Example request:

```bash
curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/events?months[]=01&years[]=1970&limit=10&offset=0" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
```

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/events"
);

let params = {
    "months[]": "01",
    "years[]": "1970",
    "limit": "10",
    "offset": "0",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```


> Example response (200):

```json
null
```
> Example response (500):

```json
{
    "Response": false,
    "StatusCode": 500,
    "Message": "Something wen't wrong",
    "Result": []
}
```
> Example response (404):

```json
{
    "Response": false,
    "StatusCode": 404,
    "Message": "No records found",
    "Result": []
}
```

`GET api/v1/app/events`

#### Query Parameters

Parameter | Status | Description
--------- | ------- | ------- | -----------
    `months[0]` |  required  | date array.
    `years[0]` |  required  | date array.

    `offset` |  required  | integer.

## Get Previous Result

<br><small style="padding: 1px 9px 2px;font-weight: bold;white-space: nowrap;color: #ffffff;-webkit-border-radius: 9px;-moz-border-radius: 9px;border-radius: 9px;background-color: #3a87ad;">Requires authentication</small>
> Example request:

```bash
curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/get-previous-result?exercise_id=dignissimos" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
```

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/get-previous-result"
);

let params = {
    "exercise_id": "dignissimos",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```

> Example request:

```bash
curl -X POST \

    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"assignment_id":"rerum","exercise_id":"mollitia","level_id":"placeat"}'
```

## Share Post

<br><small style="padding: 1px 9px 2px;font-weight: bold;white-space: nowrap;color: #ffffff;-webkit-border-radius: 9px;-moz-border-radius: 9px;border-radius: 9px;background-color: #3a87ad;">Requires authentication</small>
> Example request:

```bash
curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/share-post" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    -d '{"player_exercise_id":"ut","description":"qui"}'

```

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/share-post"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

let body = {
    "player_exercise_id": "ut",
    "description": "qui"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```


> Example response (200):

```json
null
```

#Home


APIs for home feeds
<!-- START_3752ce524505ac39862f6d6535094957 -->
## api/v1/app/home/feeds
> Example request:

```bash
curl -X GET \
    -G "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/home/feeds" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
```

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/home/feeds"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```


> Example response (200):

```json
{
    "Response": false,
    "StatusCode": 401,
    "Message": "Unauthenticated user to access this route",
    "Result": {}
}
```

<br><small style="padding: 1px 9px 2px;font-weight: bold;white-space: nowrap;color: #ffffff;-webkit-border-radius: 9px;-moz-border-radius: 9px;border-radius: 9px;background-color: #3a87ad;">Requires authentication</small>
Adding/Updating story of the current player

> Example request:

```bash
curl -X POST \
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/stories/add-edit?story_id=doloremque&thumbnail=possimus&media=accusamus" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Accept: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
```

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "https://dev.api.433pro.by433.com/api/v1/app/stories/add-edit"
);

let params = {
    "story_id": "doloremque",
    "thumbnail": "possimus",
    "media": "accusamus",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```


> Example response (200):

```json
{
    "Response": true,
    "StatusCode": 200,
    "Message": "Record has been saved",
    "Result": {
        "author_id": 106,
        "thumbnail": "media\/stories\/thumbnails\/5fc55827e03e91606768679.jpeg",
        "media": "media\/stories\/5fc55827e3d141606768679.jpeg",
        "media_type": "jpeg",
        "updated_at": "2020-11-30 20:37:59",
        "created_at": "2020-11-30 20:37:59",
        "id": 2
    }
}
```

### HTTP Request
`POST api/v1/app/stories/add-edit`

#### Query Parameters

Parameter | Status | Description
--------- | ------- | ------- | -----------
    `story_id` |  optional  | optional
    `thumbnail` |  required  | 
    `media` |  required  |
